Here is the link to the [http://research.yale.edu/isp/a2k/wiki/index.php/Peer_Production_and_Education_Panel, Peer Production and Education Panel wiki].  The panel took place at the [http://research.yale.edu/isp/eventsa2k.html, Yale Access to Knowledge Conference], 21-22 April 2006. 
 
Andy Carvin (Coordinator at the [http://www.digitaldivide.net, Digital Divide Network]) moderated a panel that included Jennifer Correiro (Co-founder and ED of [http://takingitglobal.org/, “Taking it Global"]), Steve Midgley ([http://www.stupski.org, Stupski Foundation]), Saskia Harmsen  ([http://www.iicd.org, International Institute for Communication and Development]), and Jac Stienen ([http://www.iicd.org, International Institute for Communication and Development]).

